  "answer": {
    "role": "assistant",
    "content": "<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"UTF-8\" />\n<meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1\" />\n<title>Interactive Exploration of Type Systems</title>\n<style>\n  /* Minimal styling: plain black text on white background */\n  body {\n    font-family: monospace, monospace;\n    padding: 1em;\n    margin: 0;\n    background: white;\n    color: black;\n  }\n  input, select, button, textarea {\n    font-family: monospace;\n    font-size: 1em;\n    margin: 0.2em 0;\n  }\n  label {\n    display: block;\n    margin-top: 1em;\n  }\n  pre {\n    background: #fff;\n    white-space: pre-wrap;\n    max-height: 300px;\n    overflow-y: auto;\n    border: 1px solid #ccc;\n    padding: 0.5em;\n    margin-top: 0.5em;\n  }\n  hr {\n    margin: 2em 0;\n  }\n</style>\n</head>\n<body>\n<h1>Interactive Exploration of Type Systems</h1>\n<p>\n  This tool lets you experiment with different type system features, create custom types,\n  build expressions, and see how typing rules apply step by step.\n</p>\n\n<!-- Section 1: Choose type system features -->\n<section id=\"features-section\">\n  <h2>1. Select Type System Features</h2>\n  <label><input type=\"checkbox\" id=\"feature-basic\" checked disabled> Basic Types (Int, Bool, String)</label>\n  <label><input type=\"checkbox\" id=\"feature-algebraic\" /> Algebraic Data Types (Sum and Product)</label>\n  <label><input type=\"checkbox\" id=\"feature-polymorphism\" /> Parametric Polymorphism (Generics)</label>\n  <label><input type=\"checkbox\" id=\"feature-subtyping\" /> Subtyping and Type Hierarchies</label>\n  <label><input type=\"checkbox\" id=\"feature-typeinference\" /> Type Inference</label>\n  <label><input type=\"checkbox\" id=\"feature-dependent\" /> Dependent Types (limited)</label>\n  <button id=\"apply-features\">Apply Features</button>\n  <pre id=\"output-features\" aria-live=\"polite\"></pre>\n</section>\n\n<hr />\n\n<!-- Section 2: Define custom types -->\n<section id=\"types-section\" style=\"display:none;\">\n  <h2>2. Define Custom Types</h2>\n  <p>Define new types as algebraic data types using the syntax below, if enabled:</p>\n  <p><code>type TypeName a b = Constructor1 Type1 Type2 | Constructor2 Type3 | ...</code></p>\n  <p>Example: <code>type Maybe a = Just a | Nothing</code></p>\n  <label for=\"type-definition\">Your type definition:</label>\n  <textarea id=\"type-definition\" rows=\"4\" cols=\"60\"></textarea><br />\n  <button id=\"add-type\">Add/Update Type</button>\n  <button id=\"list-types\">List Defined Types</button>\n  <pre id=\"output-types\" aria-live=\"polite\"></pre>\n</section>\n\n<hr />\n\n<!-- Section 3: Create expressions -->\n<section id=\"expressions-section\" style=\"display:none;\">\n  <h2>3. Create Expressions</h2>\n  <p>Create expressions using variables, literals, functions, and type constructors.</p>\n  <p>Supported expression syntax (depends on enabled features):</p>\n  <pre>\n- Literals: 1, true, false, \"text\"\n- Variables: x, y, z ...\n- Lambda: \\x -> expr\n- Application: f x\n- Let: let x = expr1 in expr2\n- Constructors: Just 5, Nothing\n- Polymorphic functions: id, const (pre-defined)\n  </pre>\n  <label for=\"expression-input\">Enter expression:</label><br />\n  <textarea id=\"expression-input\" rows=\"3\" cols=\"60\"></textarea><br />\n  <button id=\"check-type\">Check Expression Type</button>\n  <button id=\"show-derivation\">Show Typing Derivation</button>\n  <pre id=\"output-expression\" aria-live=\"polite\"></pre>\n</section>\n\n<hr />\n\n<!-- Section 4: Advanced type system control -->\n<section id=\"advanced-section\" style=\"display:none;\">\n  <h2>4. Advanced Controls and Exploration</h2>\n  <p>Adjust type inference and subtyping behavior:</p>\n  <label>\n    Type Inference Strategy:\n    <select id=\"inference-strategy\">\n      <option value=\"simple\">Simple (Hindley-Milner style)</option>\n      <option value=\"bidirectional\">Bidirectional</option>\n      <option value=\"none\">Disabled (Explicit annotations only)</option>\n    </select>\n  </label>\n\n  <label>\n    Subtyping:\n    <select id=\"subtyping-strategy\">\n      <option value=\"none\">None</option>\n      <option value=\"nominal\">Nominal Subtyping</option>\n      <option value=\"structural\">Structural Subtyping</option>\n    </select>\n  </label>\n\n  <label>\n    Enable Dependent Types:\n    <input type=\"checkbox\" id=\"enable-dependent\" />\n  </label>\n\n  <button id=\"apply-advanced\">Apply Advanced Settings</button>\n  <pre id=\"output-advanced\" aria-live=\"polite\"></pre>\n</section>\n\n<hr />\n\n<!-- Section 5: History and Undo -->\n<section id=\"history-section\" style=\"display:none;\">\n  <h2>5. Interaction History and Undo</h2>\n  <button id=\"undo-button\">Undo Last Action</button>\n  <button id=\"redo-button\">Redo Last Undone</button>\n  <button id=\"clear-history-button\">Clear History</button>\n  <pre id=\"history-output\" aria-live=\"polite\" style=\"max-height: 150px; overflow-y: auto;\"></pre>\n</section>\n\n<script>\n(() => {\n  // Data structures for representing types, environment, expressions, derivations\n\n  // ==== Utility Functions ====\n  function logOutput(elem, text) {\n    elem.textContent = text || \"\";\n  }\n  function appendOutput(elem, text) {\n    elem.textContent += text;\n  }\n  function deepClone(obj) {\n    return JSON.parse(JSON.stringify(obj));\n  }\n  function isAlpha(c) {\n    return /^[a-zA-Z_]$/.test(c);\n  }\n  function isAlphaNum(c) {\n    return /^[a-zA-Z0-9_]$/.test(c);\n  }\n\n  // ==== Type System Representation ====\n\n  // Basic primitive types\n  class Type {\n    constructor(kind) {\n      this.kind = kind || \"unknown\"; // e.g. \"int\", \"bool\", \"fun\", \"var\", \"adt\", \"poly\"\n    }\n    toString() {\n      return \"<Type>\";\n    }\n  }\n\n  class TInt extends Type {\n    constructor() {\n      super(\"int\");\n    }\n    toString() {\n      return \"Int\";\n    }\n  }\n\n  class TBool extends Type {\n    constructor() {\n      super(\"bool\");\n    }\n    toString() {\n      return \"Bool\";\n    }\n  }\n\n  class TString extends Type {\n    constructor() {\n      super(\"string\");\n    }\n    toString() {\n      return \"String\";\n    }\n  }\n\n  // Type variable - for polymorphism and inference\n  class TVar extends Type {\n    constructor(name) {\n      super(\"var\");\n      this.name = name;\n      this.instance = null; // For unification, instantiation\n    }\n    toString() {\n      if (this.instance) return this.instance.toString();\n      return this.name;\n    }\n  }\n\n  // Function type\n  class TFun extends Type {\n    constructor(from, to) {\n      super(\"fun\");\n      this.from = from;\n      this.to = to;\n    }\n    toString() {\n      let fromStr = this.from.kind === \"fun\" ? `(${this.from.toString()})` : this.from.toString();\n      return fromStr + \" -> \" + this.to.toString();\n    }\n  }\n\n  // Algebraic Data Type - sum/product type\n  class TADT extends Type {\n    constructor(name, parameters) {\n      super(\"adt\");\n      this.name = name;\n      this.parameters = parameters || []; // Type[]\n    }\n    toString() {\n      if (this.parameters.length === 0) return this.name;\n      return this.name + \" \" + this.parameters.map(p => p.toString()).join(\" \");\n    }\n  }\n\n  // For dependent types (very basic representation)\n  class TDependent extends Type {\n    constructor(baseType, predicate) {\n      super(\"dependent\");\n      this.baseType = baseType;\n      this.predicate = predicate; // string (expression over value)\n    }\n    toString() {\n      return `${this.baseType.toString()} { ${this.predicate} }`;\n    }\n  }\n\n  // ==== Type Environment, Context ====\n  //\n  // Holds defined types, variables and their types, constructors, subtyping info...\n\n  class Env {\n    constructor() {\n      this.vars = new Map(); // varName -> Type\n      this.types = new Map(); // typeName -> {params: [typevars], constructors: [{name, args: [Type]}]}\n      this.constructors = new Map(); // ctorName -> typeName and arg types\n      this.subtyping = { enabled: false, strategy: \"none\", parents: new Map() }; \n      // parents: typeName -> [supertype names]\n      this.features = {\n        algebraic: false,\n        polymorphism: false,\n        subtyping: false,\n        typeinference: false,\n        dependent: false\n      };\n      this.inferenceStrategy = \"simple\";\n    }\n\n    addBasicTypes() {\n      // Basic types are predefined, no constructors\n      this.types.set(\"Int\", { params: [], constructors: [] });\n      this.types.set(\"Bool\", { params: [], constructors: [] });\n      this.types.set(\"String\", { params: [], constructors: [] });\n    }\n\n    addAlgebraicType(name, params, constructors) {\n      // constructors: [{name, args: [Type]}]\n      this.types.set(name, { params: params, constructors: constructors });\n      // register constructors globally\n      for (const c of constructors) {\n        this.constructors.set(c.name, { typeName: name, args: c.args });\n      }\n    }\n\n    getType(name) {\n      if (this.types.has(name)) return this.types.get(name);\n      return null;\n    }\n\n    hasConstructor(name) {\n      return this.constructors.has(name);\n    }\n    getConstructor(name) {\n      return this.constructors.get(name);\n    }\n\n    isSubtype(sub, sup) {\n      if (!this.features.subtyping) return false;\n      // Nominal or structural\n      if (this.subtyping.strategy === \"none\") return false;\n      if (sub.toString() === sup.toString()) return true;\n\n      if (this.subtyping.strategy === \"nominal\") {\n        // We check parents hierarchy\n        if (!sub.kind || !sup.kind) return false;\n        let subs = sub.kind === \"adt\" ? sub.name : null;\n        let sups = sup.kind === \"adt\" ? sup.name : null;\n        if (!subs || !sups) return false;\n        if (subs === sups) return true;\n        const parents = this.subtyping.parents;\n        let visited = new Set();\n        let queue = [subs];\n        while (queue.length > 0) {\n          let t = queue.shift();\n          if (t === sups) return true;\n          if (visited.has(t)) continue;\n          visited.add(t);\n          let ps = parents.get(t) || [];\n          queue.push(...ps);\n        }\n        return false;\n      }\n      if (this.subtyping.strategy === \"structural\") {\n        // Structural subtyping: e.g. record types with subset of fields, or ADTs with subsets\n        // We do a very simple approximate check: if sub's constructors are subset of sup's constructors\n        if (sub.kind !== \"adt\" || sup.kind !== \"adt\") return false;\n        let subTy = this.types.get(sub.name);\n        let supTy = this.types.get(sup.name);\n        if (!subTy || !supTy) return false;\n        // Check if all supTy constructors appear in subTy with same or wider args\n        for (const sctor of supTy.constructors) {\n          let sc = subTy.constructors.find(c => c.name === sctor.name);\n          if (!sc) return false;\n          if (sc.args.length !== sctor.args.length) return false;\n          // Check arg types compatible (very simple: equal)\n          for (let i = 0; i < sc.args.length; i++) {\n            if (sc.args[i].toString() !== sctor.args[i].toString()) return false;\n          }\n        }\n        return true;\n      }\n      return false;\n    }\n  }\n\n  // ==== Parsing and Processing User Input for Types ====\n\n  // Parse a type expression (very simplified):\n  // E.g. Int, Maybe a, (a -> b), etc.\n  function parseTypeExpr(str, env, typeVars = new Map()) {\n    // tokenization - split by spaces for simplicity\n    // This is a minimal parser supporting:\n    // - Basic types by name\n    // - type variables: single lowercase letter or string (used as polymorphic vars)\n    // - application: e.g. Maybe a\n    // - function types: a -> b (right associative)\n    // - parenthesis (not implemented for simplicity)\n    let tokens = str.match(/->|[()|]|[a-zA-Z_][a-zA-Z0-9_]*|./g);\n    if (!tokens) return null;\n\n    // We'll parse right-associative function at top-level so:\n    // parse function types split by '->'\n    let parts = str.split(/\\s*->\\s*/);\n    if (parts.length > 1) {\n      // parse left and right recursively\n      let left = parseTypeExpr(parts.slice(0, -1).join(\"->\"), env, typeVars);\n      let right = parseTypeExpr(parts[parts.length - 1], env, typeVars);\n      if (!left || !right) return null;\n      return new TFun(left, right);\n    }\n\n    // No ->, parse application or basic\n    let tokens2 = parts[0].trim().split(/\\s+/).filter(t => t.length > 0);\n    if (tokens2.length === 0) return null;\n    let first = tokens2[0];\n    if (env.types.has(first)) {\n      if (tokens2.length === 1) return new TADT(first, []);\n      else {\n        // parse parameters\n        let params = [];\n        for (let i = 1; i < tokens2.length; i++) {\n          let t = tokens2[i];\n          let p = null;\n          if (typeVars.has(t)) {\n            p = typeVars.get(t);\n          } else {\n            p = new TVar(t);\n            typeVars.set(t, p);\n          }\n          params.push(p);\n        }\n        return new TADT(first, params);\n      }\n    } else if (/^[a-z][a-zA-Z0-9_]*$/.test(first)) {\n      // type variable\n      if (!typeVars.has(first)) typeVars.set(first, new TVar(first));\n      if (tokens2.length === 1) return typeVars.get(first);\n      // Not applying a variable; invalid?\n      return null;\n    } else if (first === \"Int\") return new TInt();\n    else if (first === \"Bool\") return new TBool();\n    else if (first === \"String\") return new TString();\n\n    return null;\n  }\n\n  // Parse a type definition string (e.g. `type Maybe a = Just a | Nothing`)\n  // Returns object: {name, params, constructors} or null on error\n  function parseTypeDefinition(str, env) {\n    let lines = str.trim().split(/\\n/).map(l => l.trim()).filter(l => l.length > 0);\n    if (lines.length !== 1) return { error: \"Only one line type definitions supported\" };\n    let line = lines[0];\n    if (!line.startsWith(\"type \")) return { error: \"Type definition must start with 'type'\" };\n    let afterType = line.slice(5).trim();\n    // split at = sign\n    let eqIndex = afterType.indexOf(\"=\");\n    if (eqIndex < 0) return { error: \"Missing '=' in type definition\" };\n    let head = afterType.slice(0, eqIndex).trim();\n    let body = afterType.slice(eqIndex + 1).trim();\n    // head: TypeName [params...]\n    let parts = head.split(/\\s+/);\n    if (parts.length === 0) return { error: \"Invalid type name in definition\" };\n    let name = parts[0];\n    let params = parts.slice(1);\n\n    // Parse constructors: separated by |\n    let ctorStrs = body.split(\"|\").map(s => s.trim()).filter(s => s.length > 0);\n    if (ctorStrs.length === 0) return { error: \"No constructors found\" };\n\n    let typeVars = new Map();\n    params.forEach(p => typeVars.set(p, new TVar(p)));\n\n    let constructors = [];\n\n    for (const ctorStr of ctorStrs) {\n      // first word is constructor name, rest are argument types\n      let cparts = ctorStr.split(/\\s+/).filter(x => x.length > 0);\n      if (cparts.length === 0) {\n        return { error: \"Empty constructor definition\" };\n      }\n      let ctorName = cparts[0];\n      let ctorArgs = [];\n      for (let i = 1; i < cparts.length; i++) {\n        let t = parseTypeExpr(cparts[i], env, typeVars);\n        if (!t) return { error: `Invalid type expression: '${cparts[i]}' in constructor '${ctorName}'` };\n        ctorArgs.push(t);\n      }\n      constructors.push({ name: ctorName, args: ctorArgs });\n    }\n\n    return { name, params, constructors };\n  }\n\n  // ==== Expression AST and Parsing ====\n\n  // Expressions:\n  // literal: IntLiteral, BoolLiteral, StringLiteral\n  // var: Var\n  // lambda: Lambda(param, body)\n  // application: Apply(fun, arg)\n  // let: Let(var, expr, body)\n  // constructor application: Constructor(name, args)\n  // We parse a simplified expression language supporting these forms\n\n  // AST node classes\n\n  class Expr {\n    constructor(kind) {\n      this.kind = kind;\n    }\n    toString() {\n      return \"<Expr>\";\n    }\n  }\n\n  class IntLiteral extends Expr {\n    constructor(value) {\n      super(\"int_lit\");\n      this.value = value;\n    }\n    toString() {\n      return this.value.toString();\n    }\n  }\n  class BoolLiteral extends Expr {\n    constructor(value) {\n      super(\"bool_lit\");\n      this.value = value;\n    }\n    toString() {\n      return this.value ? \"true\" : \"false\";\n    }\n  }\n  class StringLiteral extends Expr {\n    constructor(value) {\n      super(\"str_lit\");\n      this.value = value;\n    }\n    toString() {\n      return `\"${this.value}\"`;\n    }\n  }\n\n  class Var extends Expr {\n    constructor(name) {\n      super(\"var\");\n      this.name = name;\n    }\n    toString() {\n      return this.name;\n    }\n  }\n\n  class Lambda extends Expr {\n    constructor(param, body) {\n      super(\"lambda\");\n      this.param = param;\n      this.body = body;\n    }\n    toString() {\n      return `\\\\${this.param} -> ${this.body.toString()}`;\n    }\n  }\n\n  class Apply extends Expr {\n    constructor(func, arg) {\n      super(\"apply\");\n      this.func = func;\n      this.arg = arg;\n    }\n    toString() {\n      let funcStr = this.func.kind === \"lambda\" ? `(${this.func.toString()})` : this.func.toString();\n      let argStr = this.arg.kind === \"apply\" || this.arg.kind === \"lambda\" ? `(${this.arg.toString()})` : this.arg.toString();\n      return `${funcStr} ${argStr}`;\n    }\n  }\n\n  class Let extends Expr {\n    constructor(name, expr, body) {\n      super(\"let\");\n      this.name = name;\n      this.expr = expr;\n      this.body = body;\n    }\n    toString() {\n      return `let ${this.name} = ${this.expr.toString()} in ${this.body.toString()}`;\n    }\n  }\n\n  class Constructor extends Expr {\n    constructor(name, args) {\n      super(\"constructor\");\n      this.name = name;\n      this.args = args || [];\n    }\n    toString() {\n      if (this.args.length === 0) return this.name;\n      return this.name + \" \" + this.args.map(a => a.toString()).join(\" \");\n    }\n  }\n\n  // ==== Expression parser ====\n  // We parse a simplified expression set:\n  // Support:\n  // - literals: integers, true/false, strings (\"text\")\n  // - variables (alphanumeric + _)\n  // - lambdas: \\x -> expr\n  // - application: left-associative f x y\n  // - let: let x = expr in expr\n  // - constructors: names matching constructors with args: Just 5\n  // Parser is recursive descent but minimal\n\n  function tokenizeExpr(str) {\n    let result = [];\n    let i = 0;\n    while (i < str.length) {\n      let c = str[i];\n      if (/\\s/.test(c)) {\n        i++;\n        continue;\n      }\n      if (c === \"(\" || c === \")\" || c === \"\\\\\" || c === \"->\") {\n        if (c === \"-\" && str[i + 1] === \">\") {\n          result.push(\"->\");\n          i += 2;\n          continue;\n        }\n        result.push(c);\n        i++;\n        continue;\n      }\n      if (c === '\"') {\n        // string literal\n        let j = i + 1;\n        let found = false;\n        let val = \"\";\n        while (j < str.length) {\n          if (str[j] === '\"') {\n            found = true;\n            break;\n          }\n          if (str[j] === \"\\\\\") {\n            if (j + 1 < str.length) {\n              val += str[j + 1];\n              j += 2;\n            } else {\n              val += \"\\\\\";\n              j++;\n            }\n          } else {\n            val += str[j];\n            j++;\n          }\n        }\n        if (!found) return null;\n        result.push({ type: \"string\", value: val });\n        i = j + 1;\n        continue;\n      }\n      if (/[0-9]/.test(c)) {\n        // digit literal\n        let j = i + 1;\n        while (j < str.length && /[0-9]/.test(str[j])) j++;\n        let val = str.slice(i, j);\n        result.push({ type: \"int\", value: parseInt(val, 10) });\n        i = j;\n        continue;\n      }\n      // variable or keyword or constructor\n      if (/[a-zA-Z_]/.test(c)) {\n        let j = i + 1;\n        while (j < str.length && /[a-zA-Z0-9_]/.test(str[j])) j++;\n        let val = str.slice(i, j);\n        result.push(val);\n        i = j;\n        continue;\n      }\n      \n      // unrecognized character - just push as is\n      result.push(c);\n      i++;\n    }\n    return result;\n  }\n\n  function parseExpression(tokens, env) {\n    // Entry point: parse let expressions or lambda or application\n    // returns {expr, restTokens} or null\n    function parseLet(tokens) {\n      if (tokens.length === 0 || tokens[0] !== \"let\") return null;\n      tokens = tokens.slice(1);\n      if (tokens.length === 0 || typeof tokens[0] !== \"string\") return null;\n      let varName = tokens[0];\n      tokens = tokens.slice(1);\n      if (tokens.length === 0 || tokens[0] !== \"=\") return null;\n      tokens = tokens.slice(1);\n      let valParse = parseExpr(tokens);\n      if (!valParse) return null;\n      let valExpr = valParse.expr;\n      tokens = valParse.restTokens;\n      if (tokens.length === 0 || tokens[0] !== \"in\") return null;\n      tokens = tokens.slice(1);\n      let bodyParse = parseExpr(tokens);\n      if (!bodyParse) return null;\n      let bodyExpr = bodyParse.expr;\n      tokens = bodyParse.restTokens;\n      return { expr: new Let(varName, valExpr, bodyExpr), restTokens: tokens };\n    }\n\n    function parseLambda(tokens) {\n      if (tokens.length === 0 || tokens[0] !== \"\\\\\") return null;\n      tokens = tokens.slice(1);\n      if (tokens.length === 0 || typeof tokens[0] !== \"string\") return null;\n      let param = tokens[0];\n      tokens = tokens.slice(1);\n      if (tokens.length === 0 || tokens[0] !== \"->\") return null;\n      tokens = tokens.slice(1);\n      let bodyParse = parseExpr(tokens);\n      if (!bodyParse) return null;\n      return { expr: new Lambda(param, bodyParse.expr), restTokens: bodyParse.restTokens };\n    }\n\n    function parseAtom(tokens) {\n      if (tokens.length === 0) return null;\n      let t = tokens[0];\n      if (typeof t === \"object\") {\n        if (t.type === \"int\") return { expr: new IntLiteral(t.value), restTokens: tokens.slice(1) };\n        if (t.type === \"bool\") return { expr: new BoolLiteral(t.value), restTokens: tokens.slice(1) };\n        if (t.type === \"string\") return { expr: new StringLiteral(t.value), restTokens: tokens.slice(1) };\n      }\n      if (t === \"(\") {\n        // find matching )\n        let depth = 1;\n        let i = 1;\n        while (i < tokens.length && depth > 0) {\n          if (tokens[i] === \"(\") depth++;\n          else if (tokens[i] === \")\") depth--;\n          i++;\n        }\n        if (depth > 0) return null;\n        let insideTokens = tokens.slice(1, i - 1);\n        let insideParse = parseExpr(insideTokens);\n        if (!insideParse) return null;\n        let restTokens = tokens.slice(i);\n        return { expr: insideParse.expr, restTokens: restTokens };\n      }\n\n      if (typeof t === \"string\") {\n        // literal bool\n        if (t === \"true\") return { expr: new BoolLiteral(true), restTokens: tokens.slice(1) };\n        if (t === \"false\") return { expr: new BoolLiteral(false), restTokens: tokens.slice(1) };\n        // it's either var or constructor\n\n        // We try to parse constructor application:\n        if (env.hasConstructor(t)) {\n          let ctor = t;\n          tokens = tokens.slice(1);\n          // parse zero or more args until next token is operator or end or reserved keyword\n          let args = [];\n          while (tokens.length > 0) {\n            let next = tokens[0];\n            if ([\"in\", \"let\", \"=\", \"\\\\\", \"->\", \")\", \"(\"].includes(next)) break;\n            // parse atom for each arg\n            let argParsed = parseAtom(tokens);\n            if (!argParsed) break;\n            args.push(argParsed.expr);\n            tokens = argParsed.restTokens;\n          }\n          return { expr: new Constructor(ctor, args), restTokens: tokens };\n        }\n\n        // variable\n        return { expr: new Var(t), restTokens: tokens.slice(1) };\n      }\n      return null;\n    }\n\n    // Parse applications: left-associative application chain of atoms\n    let atomParsed = parseAtom(tokens);\n    if (!atomParsed) return null;\n    let expr = atomParsed.expr;\n    let restTokens = atomParsed.restTokens;\n\n    while (restTokens.length > 0) {\n      // Attempt parse next atom for application\n      let nextAtom = parseAtom(restTokens);\n      if (!nextAtom) break;\n      expr = new Apply(expr, nextAtom.expr);\n      restTokens = nextAtom.restTokens;\n    }\n    return { expr, restTokens };\n  }\n\n  function parseExpr(tokens) {\n    if (tokens.length === 0) return null;\n\n    // let expression?\n    if (tokens[0] === \"let\") {\n      let res = parseLet(tokens);\n      if (res) return res;\n    }\n    // lambda?\n    if (tokens[0] === \"\\\\\") {\n      let res = parseLambda(tokens);\n      if (res) return res;\n    }\n    // else parse application chain\n    return parseExpression(tokens);\n  }\n\n  function parseExpressionFromString(str, env) {\n    let tokens = tokenizeExpr(str);\n    if (!tokens) return null;\n    let res = parseExpr(tokens);\n    if (!res || res.restTokens.length > 0) return null;\n    return res.expr;\n  }\n\n  // ==== Type Checking and Inference ====\n\n  // Simple Hindley-Milner style inference (if enabled)\n  // Environment for inference: maps varName -> scheme (type with quantifiers)\n  // For simplicity, no full polymorphic type schemes: just type variables managed by unifier\n\n  class TypeInferenceError extends Error {\n    constructor(msg) {\n      super(msg);\n      this.name = \"TypeInferenceError\";\n    }\n  }\n\n  // Unifier for type variables\n  class TypeUnifier {\n    constructor() {\n      this.substitution = new Map(); // TVar name => Type\n    }\n    occursCheck(tv, type) {\n      if (type instanceof TVar) {\n        if (tv.name === type.name) return true;\n        if (this.substitution.has(type.name)) return this.occursCheck(tv, this.substitution.get(type.name));\n        return false;\n      } else if (type instanceof TFun) {\n        return this.occursCheck(tv, type.from) || this.occursCheck(tv, type.to);\n      } else if (type instanceof TADT) {\n        for (const p of type.parameters) {\n          if (this.occursCheck(tv, p)) return true;\n        }\n        return false;\n      }\n      return false;\n    }\n    unify(t1, t2) {\n      t1 = this.prune(t1);\n      t2 = this.prune(t2);\n\n      if (t1 instanceof TVar) {\n        if (t1.name === t2.name) return;\n        if (this.occursCheck(t1, t2)) throw new TypeInferenceError(`Recursive unification: ${t1.name} and ${t2.toString()}`);\n        this.substitution.set(t1.name, t2);\n        return;\n      }\n      if (t2 instanceof TVar) {\n        return this.unify(t2, t1);\n      }\n      if (t1.kind !== t2.kind) throw new TypeInferenceError(`Type mismatch: ${t1.toString()} vs ${t2.toString()}`);\n\n      if (t1.kind === \"int\" || t1.kind === \"bool\" || t1.kind === \"string\") return;\n\n      if (t1.kind === \"fun\") {\n        this.unify(t1.from, t2.from);\n        this.unify(t1.to, t2.to);\n        return;\n      }\n      if (t1.kind === \"adt\") {\n        if (t1.name !== t2.name) throw new TypeInferenceError(`Different ADT types: ${t1.toString()} vs ${t2.toString()}`);\n        if (t1.parameters.length !== t2.parameters.length) throw new TypeInferenceError(`Parameter length mismatch in ${t1.toString()}`);\n        for (let i = 0; i < t1.parameters.length; i++) {\n          this.unify(t1.parameters[i], t2.parameters[i]);\n        }\n        return;\n      }\n      throw new TypeInferenceError(`Unsupported unification: ${t1.toString()} vs ${t2.toString()}`);\n    }\n    prune(type) {\n      if (type instanceof TVar) {\n        if (this.substitution.has(type.name)) {\n          let t = this.substitution.get(type.name);\n          let p = this.prune(t);\n          this.substitution.set(type.name, p);\n          return p;\n        }\n      }\n      return type;\n    }\n  }\n\n  // Type Environment for inference: var -> Type (possibly generic)\n  class TypeEnv {\n    constructor() {\n      this.env = new Map();\n    }\n    extend(name, ty) {\n      let nenv = new TypeEnv();\n      for (const [k,v] of this.env.entries()) nenv.env.set(k, v);\n      nenv.env.set(name, ty);\n      return nenv;\n    }\n    lookup(name) {\n      return this.env.get(name) || null;\n    }\n  }\n\n  // We predefine some polymorphic functions if polymorphism enabled\n  const PREDEFINED_POLYMORPHIC_FUNCTIONS = {\n    id: null,    // \\a -> a\n    const: null  // \\a b -> a\n  };\n\n  // Type substitution helper for polymorphic vars (instantiate)\n  function freshTypeVarFactory() {\n    let count = 0;\n    return () => new TVar(`t${count++}`);\n  }\n\n  // Infer type for expression in given environment, using unifier.\n  // Returns inferred Type and derivation steps.\n  function inferType(expr, env, typeEnv, unifier, freshVarGen, derivation) {\n    if (!derivation) derivation = [];\n    if (!typeEnv) typeEnv = new TypeEnv();\n    if (!unifier) unifier = new TypeUnifier();\n    if (!freshVarGen) freshVarGen = freshTypeVarFactory();\n\n    function infer(e) {\n      if (e.kind === \"int_lit\") {\n        derivation.push(`Literal integer ${e.value} has type Int`);\n        return new TInt();\n      }\n      if (e.kind === \"bool_lit\") {\n        derivation.push(`Literal boolean ${e.value} has type Bool`);\n        return new TBool();\n      }\n      if (e.kind === \"str_lit\") {\n        derivation.push(`Literal string \"${e.value}\" has type String`);\n        return new TString();\n      }\n      if (e.kind === \"var\") {\n        let t = typeEnv.lookup(e.name);\n        if (t) {\n          derivation.push(`Variable '${e.name}' has type ${t.toString()} (from environment)`);\n          return t;\n        }\n        // if predefined polymorphic functions enabled\n        if (env.features.polymorphism && e.name === \"id\") {\n          // id : a -> a\n          let a = freshVarGen();\n          let idType = new TFun(a, a);\n          derivation.push(`Variable 'id' is polymorphic function of type ${idType.toString()}`);\n          return idType;\n        }\n        if (env.features.polymorphism && e.name === \"const\") {\n          // const : a -> b -> a\n          let a = freshVarGen();\n          let b = freshVarGen();\n          let constType = new TFun(a, new TFun(b, a));\n          derivation.push(`Variable 'const' is polymorphic function of type ${constType.toString()}`);\n          return constType;\n        }\n        throw new TypeInferenceError(`Unbound variable: ${e.name}`);\n      }\n      if (e.kind === \"lambda\") {\n        let a = freshVarGen();\n        let newEnv = typeEnv.extend(e.param, a);\n        derivation.push(`Assume parameter '${e.param}' has new type variable ${a.toString()}`);\n        let b = inferInEnv(e.body, newEnv);\n        let fnType = new TFun(a, b);\n        derivation.push(`Lambda '\\\\${e.param} -> ...' has type ${fnType.toString()}`);\n        return fnType;\n      }\n      if (e.kind === \"apply\") {\n        let tfun = infer(e.func);\n        let targ = infer(e.arg);\n        let res = freshVarGen();\n        derivation.push(`Application function type: ${tfun.toString()}`);\n        derivation.push(`Application argument type: ${targ.toString()}`);\n        try {\n          unifier.unify(tfun, new TFun(targ, res));\n          let pr_res = unifier.prune(res);\n          derivation.push(`Unify function type with argument type: result type is ${pr_res.toString()}`);\n          return pr_res;\n        } catch (err) {\n          if (err instanceof TypeInferenceError) {\n            throw err;\n          }\n          throw new TypeInferenceError(err.message || err.toString());\n        }\n      }\n      if (e.kind === \"let\") {\n        let tbound = infer(e.expr);\n        derivation.push(`Let-binding '${e.name}' has inferred type ${tbound.toString()}`);\n        let newEnv = typeEnv.extend(e.name, tbound);\n        return inferInEnv(e.body, newEnv);\n      }\n      if (e.kind === \"constructor\") {\n        let ctor = env.getConstructor(e.name);\n        if (!ctor) throw new TypeInferenceError(`Unknown constructor ${e.name}`);\n        derivation.push(`Constructor '${e.name}' belongs to type ${ctor.typeName} with argument types [${ctor.args.map(a => a.toString()).join(\", \")}]`);\n        if (ctor.args.length !== e.args.length) throw new TypeInferenceError(`Constructor '${e.name}' expects ${ctor.args.length} arguments but got ${e.args.length}`);\n        for (let i = 0; i < ctor.args.length; i++) {\n          let targ = infer(e.args[i]);\n          try {\n            unifier.unify(ctor.args[i], targ);\n            derivation.push(`Argument ${i + 1} type matches constructor parameter type (${ctor.args[i].toString()})`);\n          } catch (err) {\n            throw new TypeInferenceError(`Constructor argument type mismatch: ${err.message || err.toString()}`);\n          }\n        }\n        let typeInst = new TADT(ctor.typeName, []);\n        derivation.push(`Constructor application has type ${typeInst.toString()}`);\n        return typeInst;\n      }\n      throw new TypeInferenceError(`Cannot infer type for expression kind: ${e.kind}`);\n    }\n\n    function inferInEnv(e, env) {\n      return infer(e);\n    }\n\n    try {\n      let inferred = infer(expr);\n      let pruned = unifier.prune(inferred);\n      derivation.push(`Final inferred type is ${pruned.toString()}`);\n      return { type: pruned, derivation };\n    } catch (ex) {\n      if (ex instanceof TypeInferenceError) {\n        derivation.push(\"Type inference error: \" + ex.message);\n        return { error: ex.message, derivation };\n      }\n      throw ex;\n    }\n  }\n\n  // ==== Typing with Subtyping ====\n\n  // Checking subtyping after inference for expressions in subtyping-enabled systems\n  // We simulate by checking if inferred type <= user expected type if provided (not asked here)\n  // For demo, we just show subtyping decision on types\n\n  // ==== Handling User Interactions and UI state ====\n\n  const env = new Env();\n  env.features.basic = true;\n  env.addBasicTypes();\n\n  let history = [];\n  let historyIndex = -1;\n\n  function pushHistory(actionDesc, snapshot) {\n    // trim forward history if undone\n    if (historyIndex < history.length - 1) {\n      history = history.slice(0, historyIndex + 1);\n    }\n    history.push({ desc: actionDesc, snapshot: deepClone(snapshot) });\n    historyIndex++;\n    updateHistoryOutput();\n  }\n\n  function undoHistory() {\n    if (historyIndex <= 0) return false;\n    historyIndex--;\n    let snap = history[historyIndex].snapshot;\n    restoreSnapshot(snap);\n    updateHistoryOutput();\n    return true;\n  }\n  function redoHistory() {\n    if (historyIndex >= history.length - 1) return false;\n    historyIndex++;\n    let snap = history[historyIndex].snapshot;\n    restoreSnapshot(snap);\n    updateHistoryOutput();\n    return true;\n  }\n  function clearHistory() {\n    history = [];\n    historyIndex = -1;\n    updateHistoryOutput();\n  }\n\n  function updateHistoryOutput() {\n    const histElem = document.getElementById(\"history-output\");\n    if (history.length === 0) {\n      histElem.textContent = \"No history.\";\n    } else {\n      let arr = [];\n      for (let i = 0; i < history.length; i++) {\n        let prefix = i === historyIndex ? \"→ \" : \"  \";\n        arr.push(prefix + history[i].desc);\n      }\n      histElem.textContent = arr.join(\"\\n\");\n    }\n  }\n\n  function getSnapshot() {\n    return {\n      envTypes: Array.from(env.types.entries()),\n      envConstructors: Array.from(env.constructors.entries()),\n      features: {...env.features},\n      subtyping: {...env.subtyping},\n      inferenceStrategy: env.inferenceStrategy,\n    };\n  }\n\n  function restoreSnapshot(snapshot) {\n    env.types = new Map(snapshot.envTypes);\n    env.constructors = new Map(snapshot.envConstructors);\n    env.features = {...snapshot.features};\n    env.subtyping = {...snapshot.subtyping};\n    env.inferenceStrategy = snapshot.inferenceStrategy;\n    // Update UI feature checkboxes accordingly:\n    document.getElementById(\"feature-algebraic\").checked = env.features.algebraic;\n    document.getElementById(\"feature-polymorphism\").checked = env.features.polymorphism;\n    document.getElementById(\"feature-subtyping\").checked = env.features.subtyping;\n    document.getElementById(\"feature-typeinference\").checked = env.features.typeinference;\n    document.getElementById(\"feature-dependent\").checked = env.features.dependent;\n    document.getElementById(\"inference-strategy\").value = env.inferenceStrategy;\n    document.getElementById(\"subtyping-strategy\").value = env.subtyping.strategy;\n    document.getElementById(\"enable-dependent\").checked = env.features.dependent;\n\n    updateFeatureSections();\n  }\n\n  // ==== UI Handlers ====\n\n  function updateFeatureSections() {\n    const typesSection = document.getElementById(\"types-section\");\n    const exprSection = document.getElementById(\"expressions-section\");\n    const advSection = document.getElementById(\"advanced-section\");\n    const historySection = document.getElementById(\"history-section\");\n\n    // algebraic types controls visible only if algebraic feature enabled\n    if (env.features.algebraic) {\n      typesSection.style.display = \"block\";\n    } else {\n      typesSection.style.display = \"none\";\n    }\n\n    // expressions depends on at least basic types present\n    exprSection.style.display = \"block\";\n\n    // advanced for advanced feature toggles\n    advSection.style.display = \"block\";\n\n    historySection.style.display = \"block\";\n  }\n\n  // Apply features button clicked\n  document.getElementById(\"apply-features\").addEventListener(\"click\", () => {\n    const algebraic = document.getElementById(\"feature-algebraic\").checked;\n    const polymorphism = document.getElementById(\"feature-polymorphism\").checked;\n    const subtyping = document.getElementById(\"feature-subtyping\").checked;\n    const typeinference = document.getElementById(\"feature-typeinference\").checked;\n    const dependent = document.getElementById(\"feature-dependent\").checked;\n\n    env.features.algebraic = algebraic;\n    env.features.polymorphism = polymorphism;\n    env.features.subtyping = subtyping;\n    env.features.typeinference = typeinference;\n    env.features.dependent = dependent;\n    env.features.basic = true;\n\n    // base types always present\n    env.types.clear();\n    env.constructors.clear();\n    env.addBasicTypes();\n\n    // Reset subtyping default\n    env.subtyping.enabled = subtyping;\n    if (subtyping) env.subtyping.strategy = \"nominal\"; else env.subtyping.strategy = \"none\";\n    env.subtyping.parents.clear();\n\n    // Clear type definitions text area and output\n    document.getElementById(\"type-definition\").value = \"\";\n    logOutput(document.getElementById(\"output-types\"), \"\");\n    // Clear expression input/output\n    document.getElementById(\"expression-input\").value = \"\";\n    logOutput(document.getElementById(\"output-expression\"), \"\");\n    // Clear advanced output\n    logOutput(document.getElementById(\"output-advanced\"), \"\");\n    // Update UI\n    updateFeatureSections();\n\n    pushHistory(\"Applied type system features\", getSnapshot());\n\n    logOutput(document.getElementById(\"output-features\"),\n      \"Features applied:\\n\" +\n      \"- Algebraic Types: \" + (algebraic ? \"Enabled\" : \"Disabled\") + \"\\n\" +\n      \"- Parametric Polymorphism: \" + (polymorphism ? \"Enabled\" : \"Disabled\") + \"\\n\" +\n      \"- Subtyping: \" + (subtyping ? \"Enabled\" : \"Disabled\") + \"\\n\" +\n      \"- Type Inference: \" + (typeinference ? \"Enabled\" : \"Disabled\") + \"\\n\" +\n      \"- Dependent Types: \" + (dependent ? \"Enabled\" : \"Disabled\") + \"\\n\");\n  });\n\n  // Add/Update type button clicked\n  document.getElementById(\"add-type\").addEventListener(\"click\", () => {\n    const defInput = document.getElementById(\"type-definition\").value.trim();\n    const output = document.getElementById(\"output-types\");\n    if (!env.features.algebraic) {\n      logOutput(output, \"Algebraic data types feature is disabled.\");\n      return;\n    }\n    if (defInput === \"\") {\n      logOutput(output, \"Please enter a type definition.\");\n      return;\n    }\n    let parsed = parseTypeDefinition(defInput, env);\n    if (parsed.error) {\n      logOutput(output, \"Parse error: \" + parsed.error);\n      return;\n    }\n    // Add type to environment\n    env.addAlgebraicType(parsed.name, parsed.params, parsed.constructors);\n    logOutput(output, `Added type '${parsed.name}' with constructors: ${parsed.constructors.map(c => c.name).join(\", \")}`);\n    pushHistory(`Defined type '${parsed.name}'`, getSnapshot());\n  });\n\n  // List defined types button clicked\n  document.getElementById(\"list-types\").addEventListener(\"click\", () => {\n    const output = document.getElementById(\"output-types\");\n    if (env.types.size === 0) {\n      logOutput(output, \"No types defined.\");\n      return;\n    }\n    let arr = [];\n    for (let [name, desc] of env.types.entries()) {\n      let paramsStr = desc.params.length > 0 ? desc.params.join(\" \") : \"\";\n      let ctorsStr = desc.constructors.length > 0\n        ? desc.constructors.map(c => c.name + \" \" + c.args.map(a => a.toString()).join(\" \")).join(\" | \")\n        : \"(none)\";\n      arr.push(`type ${name} ${paramsStr} = ${ctorsStr}`);\n    }\n    logOutput(output, arr.join(\"\\n\"));\n  });\n\n  // Check Expression Type button clicked\n  document.getElementById(\"check-type\").addEventListener(\"click\", () => {\n    const inputExpr = document.getElementById(\"expression-input\").value.trim();\n    const output = document.getElementById(\"output-expression\");\n    if (inputExpr.length === 0) {\n      logOutput(output, \"Enter an expression to check its type.\");\n      return;\n    }\n    const expr = parseExpressionFromString(inputExpr, env);\n    if (!expr) {\n      logOutput(output, \"Syntax error parsing expression.\");\n      return;\n    }\n    // infer type if enabled, else just check variables in environment\n    if (!env.features.typeinference) {\n      // Simple check only literals and vars (no inference)\n      if (expr.kind === \"var\") {\n        output.textContent = `Variable '${expr.name}' type check without inference: Unknown`;\n      } else {\n        output.textContent = \"Type inference disabled: can't check complex expressions.\";\n      }\n      return;\n    }\n    const derivation = [];\n    try {\n      let result = inferType(expr, env, null, null, null, derivation);\n      if (result.error) {\n        logOutput(output, \"Type error:\\n\" + result.error + \"\\n\\nDerivation:\\n\" + derivation.join(\"\\n\"));\n      } else {\n        logOutput(output, \"Type inference successful.\\nType: \" + result.type.toString() + \"\\n\\nDerivation:\\n\" + derivation.join(\"\\n\"));\n      }\n      pushHistory(\"Checked expression: \" + inputExpr, getSnapshot());\n    } catch (ex) {\n      logOutput(output, \"Error during type checking: \" + (ex.message || ex.toString()));\n    }\n  });\n\n  // Show Typing Derivation button clicked\n  document.getElementById(\"show-derivation\").addEventListener(\"click\", () => {\n    const inputExpr = document.getElementById(\"expression-input\").value.trim();\n    const output = document.getElementById(\"output-expression\");\n    if (inputExpr.length === 0) {\n      logOutput(output, \"Enter an expression to show typing derivation.\");\n      return;\n    }\n    const expr = parseExpressionFromString(inputExpr, env);\n    if (!expr) {\n      logOutput(output, \"Syntax error parsing expression.\");\n      return;\n    }\n    if (!env.features.typeinference) {\n      logOutput(output, \"Type inference disabled: no derivation available.\");\n      return;\n    }\n    let derivation = [];\n    try {\n      let result = inferType(expr, env, null, null, null, derivation);\n      if (result.error) {\n        logOutput(output, \"Type error:\\n\" + result.error + \"\\n\\nDerivation:\\n\" + derivation.join(\"\\n\"));\n      } else {\n        logOutput(output, \"Typing derivation steps:\\n\\n\" + derivation.join(\"\\n\"));\n      }\n    } catch (ex) {\n      logOutput(output, \"Error during typing derivation: \" + (ex.message || ex.toString()));\n    }\n  });\n\n  // Advanced settings apply button clicked\n  document.getElementById(\"apply-advanced\").addEventListener(\"click\", () => {\n    env.inferenceStrategy = document.getElementById(\"inference-strategy\").value;\n    env.subtyping.strategy = document.getElementById(\"subtyping-strategy\").value;\n    env.features.dependent = document.getElementById(\"enable-dependent\").checked;\n    let out = [];\n    out.push(\"Applied Advanced Settings:\");\n    out.push(\"Type Inference Strategy: \" + env.inferenceStrategy);\n    out.push(\"Subtyping Strategy: \" + env.subtyping.strategy);\n    out.push(\"Dependent Types: \" + (env.features.dependent ? \"Enabled\" : \"Disabled\"));\n    document.getElementById(\"output-advanced\").textContent = out.join(\"\\n\");\n    pushHistory(\"Applied advanced settings\", getSnapshot());\n  });\n\n  // History buttons\n  document.getElementById(\"undo-button\").addEventListener(\"click\", () => {\n    if (!undoHistory()) {\n      alert(\"No more undo steps.\");\n    }\n  });\n  document.getElementById(\"redo-button\").addEventListener(\"click\", () => {\n    if (!redoHistory()) {\n      alert(\"No more redo steps.\");\n    }\n  });\n  document.getElementById(\"clear-history-button\").addEventListener(\"click\", () => {\n    clearHistory();\n  });\n\n  // Begin by applying default features - simulate button press\n  document.getElementById(\"apply-features\").click();\n})();\n</script>\n</body>\n</html>"
  },
